==Etymology==

From French ''lieu'',"place", ''tenant'', "holder".

==noun==

# The lowest rank of a commissioned army officer, junior to the rank of [[captain]].  
# A naval officer whose rank is between that of [[ensign]] in the United States Navy and [[lieutenant commander]].  There are two ranks of lieutenant: [[lieutenant junior grade]] and lieutenant.
# A naval officer in the Royal Navy who holds the rank between [[sublieutenant]] and [[lieutenant commander]].
# A person who executes the plans and directives of another.

==adjective==

# A military grade junior to the grade the adjective modifies: ''lieutenant colonel'', ''lieutenant general''.